'''LYLAS''' is an [[Acronym and initialism|acronym]] of '''"Love you like a sister."'''  One uses this as a [[shorthand]] closing when using [[instant messaging]], or when writing a [[letter]], [[e-mail]], or [[Short message service|text message]] to a friend.  LYLAS implies a friendship so deep that one's esteem for the other person is comparable to the love one feels for a sister.  For example:
:Correspondent 1:  I've got to go, but I'll talk to you later!
:Correspondent 2:  Ok! LYLAS!
"LYLAS" is commonly used when signing someone's [[yearbook]]. Such usage predates its current status as [[internet slang]].

The male variation is "LYLAB," with "brother" replacing the word "sister."

